00:43:06.030 --> 00:43:09.090
It sounds like in
this world that this

00:43:09.090 --> 00:43:13.070
is a very relevant show for New
Yorkers and Americans, and just

00:43:13.070 --> 00:43:16.579
picturing it in the context of
the current political climate.

00:43:16.579 --> 00:43:18.120
When you guys did
the show in London,

00:43:18.120 --> 00:43:20.550
was there actually a difference
of reaction with the audience

00:43:20.550 --> 00:43:20.910
members?

00:43:20.910 --> 00:43:22.910
Because you guys get a
chance to talk to people,

00:43:22.910 --> 00:43:24.480
it sounds like, during the show.

00:43:24.480 --> 00:43:27.090
Was there kind of a difference
in reaction from the London

00:43:27.090 --> 00:43:29.610
audience versus the kind
of how like a New York,

00:43:29.610 --> 00:43:33.290
American audience
is interpreting it?

00:43:33.290 --> 00:43:43.780
WALLACE SHAWN: Well, yes, I
mean the play, the script was--

00:43:48.570 --> 00:43:54.860
well, some people have said even
that I have written other plays

00:43:54.860 --> 00:44:01.100
that they were annoyed to
see had the same anxieties

00:44:01.100 --> 00:44:02.344
expressed in them.

00:44:06.790 --> 00:44:14.110
And for some reason,
I mean, I know

00:44:14.110 --> 00:44:17.210
among even my own
acquaintances that there

00:44:17.210 --> 00:44:22.720
are certain people who have
been pushed over a certain edge

00:44:22.720 --> 00:44:31.140
by Trump, to almost
say to me, wow.

00:44:33.940 --> 00:44:37.380
The things that you've
been so stupidly,

00:44:37.380 --> 00:44:43.170
boringly saying
for decades, and I

00:44:43.170 --> 00:44:49.810
thought you were being
overly hysterical.

00:44:49.810 --> 00:44:55.830
I can't deny that you
were onto something.

00:44:55.830 --> 00:44:59.760
Things were not OK in
the way that I thought.

00:44:59.760 --> 00:45:02.970
I mean, people haven't put
it in exactly those words,

00:45:02.970 --> 00:45:07.130
but pretty close.

00:45:07.130 --> 00:45:16.790
And weirdly, the London audience
was pre-Brexit and pre-Trump.

00:45:16.790 --> 00:45:23.130
So there was this ability
to sort of pretend

00:45:23.130 --> 00:45:26.100
that it was about nothing,
and why were we watching it?

00:45:29.090 --> 00:45:32.630
Whereas nobody, virtually
nobody, in America

00:45:32.630 --> 00:45:34.610
is saying that.

00:45:34.610 --> 00:45:42.590
Certainly in New York nobody
is saying everything is fine

00:45:42.590 --> 00:45:46.820
and it's all going to be
great, and why are you upset?

00:45:49.400 --> 00:45:50.960
So that's just chance.

00:45:50.960 --> 00:45:55.660
I mean, maybe if we'd done
the play a year earlier,

00:45:55.660 --> 00:45:57.170
that would have
been the response.

00:45:57.170 --> 00:45:59.632
I don't know.

00:45:59.632 --> 00:46:00.954
SPEAKER 4: Thank you.

